text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia scalena is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt and Mid West regions of Western Australia.The rigid prickly shrub typically grows to a height of 0.5 to 1.5 metres (2 to 5 ft). It blooms from June to September and produces yellow flowers.
